description: Dashboard for Ubiquiti mPower mFi 6-Port and 3-Port Power Switches

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  timestamp AS "time",
  id
FROM tplink
WHERE
  $__timeFilter(timestamp)
ORDER BY timestamp

targets.query: SELECT mean("sensors_0_power") AS "Port 1" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("sensors_1_power") AS "Port 2" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("sensors_2_power") AS "Port 3" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("sensors_3_power") AS "Port 4" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("sensors_4_power") AS "Port 5" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("sensors_5_power") AS "Port 6" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("emeter_get_realtime_power") FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time($__interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("emeter_get_realtime_power") as "Power" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time(1h) FILL(0)
SELECT (mean("emeter_get_realtime_power") / 1000 * $cost ) as "apollo_power" FROM "$SmartPlug" WHERE $timeFilter GROUP BY time(1h) FILL(0)

title: Ubiquiti mFi mPower
